 Our experience does not jive with what we know the scriptures subscribe.

103
00:08:15,020 --> 00:08:21,020
 Instead, what we often hear is a form of Christianity that feels more synonymous for you and I,

104
00:08:21,020 --> 00:08:24,020
 of just living above average in our morality.

105
00:08:24,020 --> 00:08:29,020
 We're dealing with the nagging guilt of missing another quiet time.

106
00:08:29,020 --> 00:08:33,020
 Or rationalizing our sin because, man, it's not that big of a deal,

107
00:08:33,020 --> 00:08:35,020
 and it feels good whenever I frequent it,

108
00:08:35,020 --> 00:08:38,020
 and so I'm going to keep it over here as a little bit of a pet.

109
00:08:38,020 --> 00:08:41,020
 Or we feel that shameful feeling of not really wanting to share the gospel with anybody.

110
00:08:41,020 --> 00:08:44,020
 We know we should, but man, that's kind of something that someone else can do.

111
00:08:44,020 --> 00:08:48,020
 This is more synonymous with our Christian experience,

112
00:08:48,020 --> 00:08:58,020
 rather than the thrill of a theology that tells us God radically, wildly, crazily loves you.

113
00:08:58,020 --> 00:09:04,020
 We have a kind of Christian experience that does not jive with the truth

114
00:09:04,020 --> 00:09:08,020
 that there's a rush of relationship in walking with Jesus.

115
00:09:08,020 --> 00:09:10,020
 I want to give you back the thrill.

116
00:09:10,020 --> 00:09:12,020
 I want to give you back the rush.

117
00:09:12,020 --> 00:09:15,020
 I want to imbue you with all the vitality and vibrancy and energy

118
00:09:15,020 --> 00:09:19,020
 that your relationship to God is supposed to be filled with.

119
00:09:19,020 --> 00:09:23,020
 I want to get you out of knowing and playing make-believe

120
00:09:23,020 --> 00:09:28,020
 and into experiencing and realizing that all of this is true.

121
00:09:28,020 --> 00:09:31,020
 Because I think too often we move through life,

122
00:09:31,020 --> 00:09:38,020
 and we act the part, but we do not feel the part.

123
00:09:38,020 --> 00:09:41,020
 And as we come to chapter 3 in Paul's letter to the Ephesians,

124
00:09:41,020 --> 00:09:44,020
 it's the perfect place to unpack this idea

125
00:09:44,020 --> 00:09:46,020
 because Paul is writing to a group of people

126
00:09:46,020 --> 00:09:49,020
 that are living in this massive city called Ephesus.

127
00:09:49,020 --> 00:09:54,020
 Ephesus was the center of trade in the ancient Greco-Roman world.

128
00:09:54,020 --> 00:09:56,020
 It was the epicenter for Greek and Roman idol worship,

129
00:09:56,020 --> 00:10:00,020
 meaning it was this massive city with a group of young adults

130
00:10:00,020 --> 00:10:05,020
 whom Paul is writing to that is built around big business,

131
00:10:05,020 --> 00:10:09,020
 materialism, and sexual opportunity.

132
00:10:09,020 --> 00:10:10,020
 Sound familiar?

133
00:10:10,020 --> 00:10:13,020
 Paul is writing to a group of people in that sort of context,

134
00:10:13,020 --> 00:10:14,020
 and it's to them that he says,

135
00:10:14,020 --> 00:10:18,020
 "Hey, the world is promising you so much else,

136
00:10:18,020 --> 00:10:20,020
 satisfaction in all these other places,

137
00:10:20,020 --> 00:10:23,020
 and yet it's only actually found in Jesus."

138
00:10:23,020 --> 00:10:28,020
 You see, the climax of history is not in what you have materially.

139
00:10:28,020 --> 00:10:30,020
 It's not in where you live.

140
00:10:30,020 --> 00:10:33,020
 It's not in what you do occupationally.

141
00:10:33,020 --> 00:10:39,020
 It's not in what you actually--what kind of pleasure you find.

142
00:10:39,020 --> 00:10:41,020
 It's found in Jesus.

143
00:10:41,020 --> 00:10:44,020
 All of history has been pointing to this man,

144
00:10:44,020 --> 00:10:46,020
 and it's for very good reason.

145
00:10:46,020 --> 00:10:49,020
 And as we come to chapter 3, we see Paul.

146
00:10:49,020 --> 00:10:50,020
 He pivots in his letter.

147
00:10:50,020 --> 00:10:53,020
 He goes from chapters 1 and 2 where it's all orthodoxy,

148
00:10:53,020 --> 00:10:57,020
 what scholars identify as a focus on doctrine,

149
00:10:57,020 --> 00:10:59,020
 and he moves into orthopraxy after chapter 3.

150
00:10:59,020 --> 00:11:02,020
 He moves into chapters 4 and 5, and he starts talking about orthopraxy.

151
00:11:02,020 --> 00:11:04,020
 He starts to tell us how we're supposed to live.

152
00:11:04,020 --> 00:11:06,020
 In chapters 1 and 2, he only gives us one command.

153
00:11:06,020 --> 00:11:08,020
 He just tells you to remember.

154
00:11:08,020 --> 00:11:09,020
 Remember what?

155
00:11:09,020 --> 00:11:11,020
 Remember the details of the gospel,

156
00:11:11,020 --> 00:11:16,020
 the fact that Jesus, he has stepped into our reality

157
00:11:16,020 --> 00:11:19,020
 to defeat our enemy, to take out our sin,

158
00:11:19,020 --> 00:11:22,020
 to pay the cost of that on the cross,

159
00:11:22,020 --> 00:11:24,020
 to unite us to himself,

160
00:11:24,020 --> 00:11:28,020
 to be identified with us and have us identified with him,

161
00:11:28,020 --> 00:11:30,020
 and he is building a multi-ethnic community.

162
00:11:30,020 --> 00:11:32,020
 That's what Jesus has done.

163
00:11:32,020 --> 00:11:35,020
 And yet before he moves on and tells us,

164
00:11:35,020 --> 00:11:38,020
 "In light of all that, here's what you should now do,"

165
00:11:38,020 --> 00:11:40,020
 he stops.

166
00:11:40,020 --> 00:11:42,020
 He actually gets distracted

167
00:11:42,020 --> 00:11:47,020
 because he wants you and me to know what these verses say.

168
00:11:47,020 --> 00:11:52,020
 And so, in Ephesians 3, 14 and 16, he says this.

169
00:11:52,020 --> 00:11:56,020
 He says, detailing how crazy God's love is for his people,

170
00:11:56,020 --> 00:12:01,020
 he says, "For this reason, I bow my knees before the Father,

171
00:12:01,020 --> 00:12:04,020
 "from whom every family in heaven and on earth is named,

172
00:12:04,020 --> 00:12:06,020
 "that according to the riches of his glory,

173
00:12:06,020 --> 00:12:08,020
 "he may grant you to be strengthened with power

174
00:12:08,020 --> 00:12:11,020
 "through his Spirit in your inner being."

175
00:12:11,020 --> 00:12:12,020
 We'll stop right there.

176
00:12:12,020 --> 00:12:15,020
 Like, you might read this or hear it read to you

177
00:12:15,020 --> 00:12:16,020
 and it sounds like typical Bible,

178
00:12:16,020 --> 00:12:19,020
 and yet what you need to know is this is pretty melodramatic,

179
00:12:19,020 --> 00:12:21,020
 even for the apostle Paul.

180
00:12:21,020 --> 00:12:22,020
 Like, he could have just said,

181
00:12:22,020 --> 00:12:26,020
 "I pray to God that you would know you're loved."

182
00:12:26,020 --> 00:12:28,020
 Go in peace, to love, and serve the Lord, everybody.

183
00:12:28,020 --> 00:12:29,020
 But he doesn't do that.

184
00:12:29,020 --> 00:12:33,020
 He goes to an incredible level of detail,

185
00:12:33,020 --> 00:12:34,020
 a Shakespearean level of speech

186
00:12:34,020 --> 00:12:37,020
 to articulate the depth of affection that God has for us.

187
00:12:37,020 --> 00:12:38,020
 Why would he do that?

188
00:12:38,020 --> 00:12:44,020
 Well, why do men, or did men, speak poetry to their beloved?

189
00:12:44,020 --> 00:12:46,020
 (audience laughing)

190
00:12:46,020 --> 00:12:49,020
 Because men, not only then, but still today,

191
00:12:49,020 --> 00:12:52,020
 are bad at communicating their feelings.

192
00:12:52,020 --> 00:12:55,020
 It's not something that we are necessarily good at.

193
00:12:55,020 --> 00:12:59,020
 I will speak as one ambassador for the male population.

194
00:12:59,020 --> 00:13:01,020
 (audience laughing)

195
00:13:01,020 --> 00:13:05,020
 And so, because we care deeply about that person,

196
00:13:05,020 --> 00:13:11,020
 we know I cannot run the risk of speaking in a way

197
00:13:11,020 --> 00:13:13,020
 that will fall short of my feelings.

198
00:13:13,020 --> 00:13:16,020
 No, mere words will not suffice.

199
00:13:16,020 --> 00:13:19,020
 I must express my feelings instead.

200
00:13:19,020 --> 00:13:20,020
 That's what Paul is doing.

201
00:13:20,020 --> 00:13:24,020
 He's not just reciting facts about the way that God loves you.

202
00:13:24,020 --> 00:13:26,020
 He's pouring out his heart

203
00:13:26,020 --> 00:13:28,020
 so you might know just how wildly you're loved.

204
00:13:28,020 --> 00:13:29,020
 Listen to it.

205
00:13:29,020 --> 00:13:32,020
 "For this reason, I bow my knees before the Father,

206
00:13:32,020 --> 00:13:35,020
 "from whom every family in heaven and on earth is named,

207
00:13:35,020 --> 00:13:36,020
 "that according to the," what?

208
00:13:36,020 --> 00:13:39,020
 "The riches of his glory, he might grant you

209
00:13:39,020 --> 00:13:42,020
 "to be strengthened with power through his Spirit

210
00:13:42,020 --> 00:13:43,020
 "in your inner being."

211
00:13:43,020 --> 00:13:44,020
 Do you hear it?

212
00:13:44,020 --> 00:13:45,020
 That's a lot.

213
00:13:45,020 --> 00:13:47,020
 Like, the guy has a flair for the dramatic,

214
00:13:47,020 --> 00:13:49,020
 and yet he is doing all of this

215
00:13:49,020 --> 00:13:51,020
 because he just simply wants us to know

216
00:13:51,020 --> 00:13:55,020
 this is how wildly you're loved,

217
00:13:55,020 --> 00:13:58,020
 which raises another question for us.

218
00:13:58,020 --> 00:14:00,020
 Why does he feel the need to do this?

219
00:14:00,020 --> 00:14:03,020
 Like, why does he need to up the ante,

220
00:14:03,020 --> 00:14:05,020
 pour on the passion?

221
00:14:05,020 --> 00:14:06,020
 Because he knows,

222
00:14:06,020 --> 00:14:11,020
 while it would be easier to just say, "You're loved,"

223
00:14:11,020 --> 00:14:14,020
 he knows, while we know that,

224
00:14:14,020 --> 00:14:18,020
 we don't actually often believe it.

225
00:14:18,020 --> 00:14:22,020
 Sure, we know the nursery rhymes.

226
00:14:22,020 --> 00:14:24,020
 We've learned the Bible stories.

227
00:14:24,020 --> 00:14:27,020
 We've listened to the testimonies

228
00:14:27,020 --> 00:14:29,020
 of how God has reached in,

229
00:14:29,020 --> 00:14:30,020
 and he has saved people

230
00:14:30,020 --> 00:14:32,020
 from the depth of their own despair,

231
00:14:32,020 --> 00:14:34,020
 and yet, despite knowing it all,

232
00:14:34,020 --> 00:14:36,020
 when we get honest with ourselves,

233
00:14:36,020 --> 00:14:40,020
 and it boils down to the most gut-level,

234
00:14:40,020 --> 00:14:42,020
 honest place within our inner being,

235
00:14:42,020 --> 00:14:47,020
 what we know is that while it is true,

236
00:14:47,020 --> 00:14:51,020
 we don't feel it's true for us.

237
00:14:51,020 --> 00:14:53,020
 That's why Paul is praying here.

238
00:14:53,020 --> 00:14:56,020
 He wants us to grasp the love of God,

239
00:14:56,020 --> 00:14:57,020
 not just with our minds,

240
00:14:57,020 --> 00:14:59,020
 but with our own hearts.

241
00:14:59,020 --> 00:15:02,020
 He wants it to move from here down into here.

242
00:15:02,020 --> 00:15:05,020
 He wants it to permeate every faculty of your being.

243
00:15:05,020 --> 00:15:08,020
 He wants you to know what kind of impact

244
00:15:08,020 --> 00:15:12,020
 that kind of love should have in your life.

245
00:15:12,020 --> 00:15:14,020
 And so he tells us four things specifically

246
00:15:14,020 --> 00:15:16,020
 that will help us to understand

247
00:15:16,020 --> 00:15:18,020
 what the love of Jesus feels like,

248
00:15:18,020 --> 00:15:20,020
 what it actually does to a person

249
00:15:20,020 --> 00:15:22,020
 in their life.

250
00:15:22,020 --> 00:15:25,020
 And he picks it up in verse 16.

251
00:15:25,020 --> 00:15:27,020
 And so he says, "Hey, I bow my knees,

252
00:15:27,020 --> 00:15:30,020
 "so that according to the riches of his glory,

253
00:15:30,020 --> 00:15:32,020
 "he may grant you to be strengthened with power

254
00:15:32,020 --> 00:15:34,020
 "through his Spirit in your inner being."

255
00:15:34,020 --> 00:15:38,020
 You see, the first thing that Paul wants us to remind us of

256
00:15:38,020 --> 00:15:41,020
 is that Jesus gives strength in place of exhaustion.

257
00:15:41,020 --> 00:15:42,020
 That's the first point.

258
00:15:42,020 --> 00:15:46,020
 Jesus gives strength in place of exhaustion.

259
00:15:46,020 --> 00:15:48,020
 Anybody tired in here?

260
00:15:48,020 --> 00:15:50,020
 (congregation chattering)

261
00:15:50,020 --> 00:15:55,020
 It's always inevitably true that when I ask that question,

262
00:15:55,020 --> 00:15:58,020
 and yet I never cue a response,

263
00:15:58,020 --> 00:16:01,020
 people raise their hands and they lift their voices.

264
00:16:01,020 --> 00:16:03,020
 Because people just, they want to be identified.

265
00:16:03,020 --> 00:16:04,020
 Like, man, I'm tired.

266
00:16:04,020 --> 00:16:06,020
 Like, work has me beat.

267
00:16:06,020 --> 00:16:08,020
 My boss is asking way too much of me.

268
00:16:08,020 --> 00:16:11,020
 My friends, they are constantly asking me to go out.

269
00:16:11,020 --> 00:16:13,020
 It's difficult being popular.

270
00:16:13,020 --> 00:16:15,020
 I know that the weekends are coming,

271
00:16:15,020 --> 00:16:17,020
 but it feels like the weekdays are never ending.

272
00:16:17,020 --> 00:16:18,020
 I don't get enough sleep.

273
00:16:18,020 --> 00:16:21,020
 Instead, I'm awake too often and not by my own choice.

274
00:16:21,020 --> 00:16:23,020
 I would kill for a vacation.

275
00:16:23,020 --> 00:16:24,020
 I get it.

276
00:16:24,020 --> 00:16:25,020
 I understand that this is the case.

277
00:16:25,020 --> 00:16:27,020
 And yet here's what I want you to know.

278
00:16:27,020 --> 00:16:29,020
 Your tiredness is not the product

279
00:16:29,020 --> 00:16:32,020
 of what's happening outside of you.

280
00:16:32,020 --> 00:16:36,020
 It is the product of what's happening inside of you.

281
00:16:36,020 --> 00:16:37,020
 Your tiredness is not the product

282
00:16:37,020 --> 00:16:39,020
 of what's happening outside.

283
00:16:39,020 --> 00:16:41,020
 It's the product of what's happening inside.

284
00:16:41,020 --> 00:16:44,020
 Like, it's not that the work is just so crazy.

285
00:16:44,020 --> 00:16:47,020
 It's that you are desperately identifying

286
00:16:47,020 --> 00:16:50,020
 with the success your work offers,

287
00:16:50,020 --> 00:16:52,020
 and that's making you crazy.

288
00:16:52,020 --> 00:16:54,020
 It's not that your boyfriend or your girlfriend

289
00:16:54,020 --> 00:16:55,020
 is just so needy.

290
00:16:55,020 --> 00:16:57,020
 It's that you want to be needed by somebody.

291
00:16:57,020 --> 00:16:59,020
 It's not that all of your friends,

292
00:16:59,020 --> 00:17:01,020
 man, they just want too much of me.

293
00:17:01,020 --> 00:17:04,020
 It's that you want to be approved of by these people,

294
00:17:04,020 --> 00:17:07,020
 and so you drive yourself to the point of exhaustion

295
00:17:07,020 --> 00:17:09,020
 in order to achieve it.

296
00:17:09,020 --> 00:17:11,020
 It's not just that you're constantly trying

297
00:17:11,020 --> 00:17:13,020
 to measure up to everybody that's around you.

298
00:17:13,020 --> 00:17:17,020
 It's that you actually only find your value

299
00:17:17,020 --> 00:17:20,020
 in how you stack up against the competition.

300
00:17:20,020 --> 00:17:22,020
 It's not what's happening outside.

301
00:17:22,020 --> 00:17:25,020
 It's what's happening inside that is making you tired.

302
00:17:25,020 --> 00:17:27,020
 I could go on, and yet so many of us,

303
00:17:27,020 --> 00:17:30,020
 we let the outer world impact our inner lives

304
00:17:30,020 --> 00:17:31,020
 as opposed to letting our inner lives

305
00:17:31,020 --> 00:17:33,020
 impact the outer world,

306
00:17:33,020 --> 00:17:38,020
 and the results, they are exhausting.

307
00:17:38,020 --> 00:17:40,020
 I remember when I was in college,

308
00:17:40,020 --> 00:17:41,020
 and I've told this story before,

309
00:17:41,020 --> 00:17:43,020
 but it feels too perfect to pass on

310
00:17:43,020 --> 00:17:45,020
 to help make the point here,

311
00:17:45,020 --> 00:17:48,020
 how to craft a world-class resume.

312
00:17:48,020 --> 00:17:50,020
 I got really good at it, so good to the point

313
00:17:50,020 --> 00:17:51,020
 that I actually took a job

314
00:17:51,020 --> 00:17:54,020
 in helping people craft their resumes.

315
00:17:54,020 --> 00:17:55,020
 I'm not in that line of work anymore,

316
00:17:55,020 --> 00:17:56,020
 so save the emails.

317
00:17:56,020 --> 00:17:58,020
 You can find somebody else to help you with that,

318
00:17:58,020 --> 00:18:00,020
 and yet I learned all the tools of the trade.

319
00:18:00,020 --> 00:18:02,020
 I learned good action verbs.

320
00:18:02,020 --> 00:18:03,020
 I knew what it looked like to take

321
00:18:03,020 --> 00:18:05,020
 one's achievements and accolades

322
00:18:05,020 --> 00:18:08,020
 and put them on paper in a way that really impressed.

323
00:18:08,020 --> 00:18:10,020
 I knew what it looked like to format

324
00:18:10,020 --> 00:18:11,020
 and use the right fonting,

325
00:18:11,020 --> 00:18:13,020
 so that way businesses would read it,

326
00:18:13,020 --> 00:18:14,020
 and they would say, "Man, this guy or this girl

327
00:18:14,020 --> 00:18:18,020
 "actually has a leg up on the rest of our candidates."

328
00:18:18,020 --> 00:18:22,020
 I knew what it meant to self-promote

329
00:18:22,020 --> 00:18:23,020
 at the highest level possible,

330
00:18:23,020 --> 00:18:24,020
 and yet there was always one thing

331
00:18:24,020 --> 00:18:26,020
 that stood out to me as really interesting

332
00:18:26,020 --> 00:18:28,020
 when I would help people with their resumes.

333
00:18:28,020 --> 00:18:29,020
 I would ask them, "Hey, send me over

334
00:18:29,020 --> 00:18:31,020
 "whatever resume you have as of now,"

335
00:18:31,020 --> 00:18:32,020
 and so what they would send me

336
00:18:32,020 --> 00:18:34,020
 is not one page, though that's what it's supposed to be.

337
00:18:34,020 --> 00:18:37,020
 They would send me multiple pages

338
00:18:37,020 --> 00:18:40,020
 recounting all of their achievements,

339
00:18:40,020 --> 00:18:44,020
 awards, causes for recognition,

340
00:18:44,020 --> 00:18:46,020
 and what struck me about that

341
00:18:46,020 --> 00:18:49,020
 was not that they were sending me multiple pages

342
00:18:49,020 --> 00:18:50,020
 because surely one page is not enough

343
00:18:50,020 --> 00:18:53,020
 to contain my awesomeness,

344
00:18:53,020 --> 00:18:56,020
 but because one page was surely not enough

345
00:18:56,020 --> 00:19:00,020
 to impress anybody in their estimation.

346
00:19:00,020 --> 00:19:02,020
 They needed more than that.

347
00:19:02,020 --> 00:19:05,020
 They knew something was wrong on the inside,

348
00:19:05,020 --> 00:19:08,020
 and so I needed to fix myself on the outside.

349
00:19:08,020 --> 00:19:12,020
 I don't think that I'm actually genuinely enough

350
00:19:12,020 --> 00:19:13,020
 to impress anybody.

351
00:19:13,020 --> 00:19:15,020
 I'm not enough to impress anybody socially,

352
00:19:15,020 --> 00:19:18,020
 financially, professionally, romantically.

353
00:19:18,020 --> 00:19:22,020
 Spiritually speaking, I'm not enough,

354
00:19:22,020 --> 00:19:24,020
 and the case is true for so many of us.

355
00:19:24,020 --> 00:19:28,020
 That's why you wrap yourself in high-powered jobs.

356
00:19:28,020 --> 00:19:31,020
 That's why you filter your photos.

357
00:19:31,020 --> 00:19:36,020
 It's why you choose to buy the nicest brands

358
00:19:36,020 --> 00:19:37,020
 as opposed to the brands

359
00:19:37,020 --> 00:19:40,020
 which exist within your current budget.

360
00:19:40,020 --> 00:19:43,020
 It's why you choose to pursue big goals

361
00:19:43,020 --> 00:19:44,020
 that other people want

362
00:19:44,020 --> 00:19:47,020
 as opposed to the goals that you yourself want.

363
00:19:47,020 --> 00:19:48,020
 Why you chase after that job

364
00:19:48,020 --> 00:19:50,020
 as opposed to just a good job.

365
00:19:50,020 --> 00:19:52,020
 It's because you are measuring yourself up

366
00:19:52,020 --> 00:19:55,020
 in accordance with what everyone else thinks.

367
00:19:55,020 --> 00:19:59,020
 You are finding your value in the love of the world

368
00:19:59,020 --> 00:20:02,020
 and not the love of a king,

369
00:20:02,020 --> 00:20:06,020
 and the results of it are exhaustion.

370
00:20:06,020 --> 00:20:08,020
 You feel flawed on the inside,

371
00:20:08,020 --> 00:20:10,020
 so you're trying to fix yourself on the outside,

372
00:20:10,020 --> 00:20:11,020
 and here's the truth.

373
00:20:11,020 --> 00:20:16,020
 You are flawed on the inside.

374
00:20:16,020 --> 00:20:18,020
 You are dead in your trespasses and sins,

375
00:20:18,020 --> 00:20:19,020
 and yet Jesus Christ,

376
00:20:19,020 --> 00:20:22,020
 he has come to not fix you on the outside,

377
00:20:22,020 --> 00:20:24,020
 but to fix that which you cannot fix.

378
00:20:24,020 --> 00:20:27,020
 He has come to fix you on the inside.

379
00:20:27,020 --> 00:20:30,020
 He has come to give of himself,

380
00:20:30,020 --> 00:20:33,020
 to give to you all that you lack,

381
00:20:33,020 --> 00:20:38,020
 so that way you might find all that you want in him.

382
00:20:38,020 --> 00:20:43,020
 He has come to replace your exhaustion with his strength.

383
00:20:43,020 --> 00:20:45,020
 It's not just even that he has come to save you

384
00:20:45,020 --> 00:20:46,020
 from where you were.

385
00:20:46,020 --> 00:20:48,020
 The fact that you used to be back there

386
00:20:48,020 --> 00:20:50,020
 dealing with those sins and those problems

387
00:20:50,020 --> 00:20:51,020
 and all of those mistakes.

388
00:20:51,020 --> 00:20:53,020
 He's not just worried about the past.

389
00:20:53,020 --> 00:20:55,020
 He's not just saved you from that.

390
00:20:55,020 --> 00:20:58,020
 He has saved you to a glorious future.

391
00:20:58,020 --> 00:21:00,020
 He is leading you into something,

392
00:21:00,020 --> 00:21:01,020
 the likes of which will be better

393
00:21:01,020 --> 00:21:04,020
 than you could ever dare ask or imagine.

394
00:21:04,020 --> 00:21:06,020
 Don't believe me?

395
00:21:06,020 --> 00:21:09,020
 Place your faith in him and take him up on the offer.

396
00:21:09,020 --> 00:21:11,020
 See if it is better.

397
00:21:11,020 --> 00:21:13,020
 I assure you, it will be.

398
00:21:13,020 --> 00:21:15,020
 His word is true.

399
00:21:15,020 --> 00:21:17,020
 His promises are perfect.

400
00:21:17,020 --> 00:21:20,020
 He does not fail to keep his word.

401
00:21:20,020 --> 00:21:22,020
 He will lead you forward into that

402
00:21:22,020 --> 00:21:25,020
 which you could not dare dream for yourself.

403
00:21:25,020 --> 00:21:30,020
 And it's because there he is waiting for you.

404
00:21:30,020 --> 00:21:33,020
 Paul says it like this to the Corinthians

405
00:21:33,020 --> 00:21:38,020
 when talking about the inner person.

406
00:21:38,020 --> 00:21:39,020
 He says in 2 Corinthians 4, 16,

407
00:21:39,020 --> 00:21:41,020
 "So we do not lose heart.

408
00:21:41,020 --> 00:21:43,020
 Though our outer self is wasting away,

409
00:21:43,020 --> 00:21:47,020
 our inner self is being renewed day by day by day."

410
00:21:47,020 --> 00:21:50,020
 That's how much God cares about your inner person.

411
00:21:50,020 --> 00:21:52,020
 That's why in here in Ephesians 3, he says,

412
00:21:52,020 --> 00:21:55,020
 "He is literally strengthening every day by his spirit,

413
00:21:55,020 --> 00:21:58,020
 our innermost being from the inexhaustible well

414
00:21:58,020 --> 00:21:59,020
 of his glorious riches."

415
00:21:59,020 --> 00:22:01,020
 That's amazing to consider.

416
00:22:01,020 --> 00:22:04,020
 God cares a lot about how you are doing on the inside.

417
00:22:04,020 --> 00:22:10,020
 So let me ask you, how healthy is your inner life tonight?

418
00:22:10,020 --> 00:22:12,020
 How healthy is your inner life?

419
00:22:12,020 --> 00:22:16,020
 What do you see when you stare at that part of yourself

420
00:22:16,020 --> 00:22:17,020
 which no one else can see?

421
00:22:17,020 --> 00:22:21,020
 How do you feel in your soul?

422
00:22:21,020 --> 00:22:25,020
 How's your spiritual pulse doing?

423
00:22:25,020 --> 00:22:31,020
 Is it strong, beating vibrantly within your chest?

424
00:22:31,020 --> 00:22:33,020
 Or is it flatlining?

425
00:22:33,020 --> 00:22:37,020
 Are you striding with the spirit, making great ground?

426
00:22:37,020 --> 00:22:40,020
 Or are you cold, dead on the table

427
00:22:40,020 --> 00:22:42,020
 because your inner life is withering

428
00:22:42,020 --> 00:22:46,020
 while you try to keep up with the world's watching?

429
00:22:46,020 --> 00:22:47,020
 What is it for you?

430
00:22:47,020 --> 00:22:49,020
 Listen to me.

431
00:22:49,020 --> 00:22:54,020
 God's desire for your life is not a life of hopelessness

432
00:22:54,020 --> 00:22:58,020
 or exhaustion or stress or desperation or insecurity.

433
00:22:58,020 --> 00:23:00,020
 If that describes your experience, that's not his heart for you.

434
00:23:00,020 --> 00:23:02,020
 That's not his life for you.

435
00:23:02,020 --> 00:23:06,020
 Instead, his desire is that your life would flourish.

436
00:23:06,020 --> 00:23:10,020
 That you would be bursting and beaming with life.

437
00:23:10,020 --> 00:23:14,020
 That everywhere you go would be a place of flourishing.

438
00:23:14,020 --> 00:23:16,020
 Not because the circumstances are great,

439
00:23:16,020 --> 00:23:18,020
 but because he is with you in the circumstances.

440
00:23:18,020 --> 00:23:21,020
 Because he goes with you wherever it is you go.

441
00:23:21,020 --> 00:23:25,020
 Because he is the source of your life, not the things in this world.

442
00:23:25,020 --> 00:23:28,020
 You see, his love should strengthen your innermost self

443
00:23:28,020 --> 00:23:31,020
 so that when, not if, but when things go bad,

444
00:23:31,020 --> 00:23:34,020
 when failure inevitably comes, when trouble eventually strikes,

445
00:23:34,020 --> 00:23:36,020
 when hurt however happens,

446
00:23:36,020 --> 00:23:38,020
 you are still standing on the other side of it.

447
00:23:38,020 --> 00:23:43,020
 That is the first thing that the love Jesus offers does to your life.

448
00:23:43,020 --> 00:23:46,020
 That's how it should feel. It should feel like strength.

449
00:23:46,020 --> 00:23:48,020
 But that's not all.

450
00:23:48,020 --> 00:23:51,020
 The second one is in verse 17.

451
00:23:51,020 --> 00:23:55,020
 He prays that Christ may dwell in your hearts through faith.

452
00:23:55,020 --> 00:23:58,020
 That you, being rooted and grounded in love.

453
00:23:58,020 --> 00:24:00,020
 We'll stop right there.

454
00:24:00,020 --> 00:24:02,020
 It's interesting. When you read this verse in the original language,

455
00:24:02,020 --> 00:24:05,020
 because our English translations, they don't exactly do justice

456
00:24:05,020 --> 00:24:07,020
 to what Paul is meaning here.

457
00:24:07,020 --> 00:24:10,020
 When Paul says that Christ may dwell in your hearts,

458
00:24:10,020 --> 00:24:16,020
 he uses the word for dwell that means more than simply being in a house,

459
00:24:16,020 --> 00:24:19,020
 but actually means being at home.

460
00:24:19,020 --> 00:24:23,020
 Like Jesus looks at your life,

461
00:24:23,020 --> 00:24:26,020
 and he does not treat it like an Airbnb.

462
00:24:26,020 --> 00:24:29,020
 Like it's not a place that he stays at for a while,

463
00:24:29,020 --> 00:24:33,020
 but then he slips out whenever things are not up to his standard.

464
00:24:33,020 --> 00:24:36,020
 It's not that he lives in your heart,

465
00:24:36,020 --> 00:24:39,020
 but then the minute you start to misbehave, or you do something bad,

466
00:24:39,020 --> 00:24:41,020
 or you're praying enough, or man, I don't know,

467
00:24:41,020 --> 00:24:43,020
 that doesn't actually feel worthy for me.

468
00:24:43,020 --> 00:24:47,020
 When that happens, he doesn't just dip and leave you to pick up the mess.

469
00:24:47,020 --> 00:24:49,020
 He does not treat you that way.

470
00:24:49,020 --> 00:24:52,020
 No, he considers your heart his home.

471
00:24:52,020 --> 00:24:54,020
 He knows every nook and cranny.

472
00:24:54,020 --> 00:24:57,020
 He has keys to every single room.

473
00:24:57,020 --> 00:25:02,020
 And he likes it there.

474
00:25:02,020 --> 00:25:08,020
 Jesus likes making his home in your heart.

475
00:25:08,020 --> 00:25:10,020
 Anybody got homebodies in the room?

476
00:25:10,020 --> 00:25:12,020
 Anybody bold enough to raise a hand and say,

477
00:25:12,020 --> 00:25:16,020
 "Yeah, man, I'd rather be at home than go out with some people."

478
00:25:16,020 --> 00:25:19,020
 Jesus is a homebody when it comes to you.

479
00:25:19,020 --> 00:25:21,020
 He wants to be with you.

480
00:25:21,020 --> 00:25:23,020
 He wants you to take up residence inside of you.

481
00:25:23,020 --> 00:25:27,020
 He wants to dwell with you and make you into his home

482
00:25:27,020 --> 00:25:32,020
 because Jesus, the love he offers, it gives acceptance, not rejection.

483
00:25:32,020 --> 00:25:34,020
 The second point.

484
00:25:34,020 --> 00:25:38,020
 Jesus gives acceptance and not rejection,

485
00:25:38,020 --> 00:25:40,020
 which is easy to understand,

486
00:25:40,020 --> 00:25:43,020
 but it is much more difficult to believe.

487
00:25:43,020 --> 00:25:45,020
 Why?

488
00:25:45,020 --> 00:25:49,020
 Well, let me try an exercise to see if I can't illustrate this.

489
00:25:49,020 --> 00:25:55,020
 What I want you to do is I want you to hear the question I ask in a moment,

490
00:25:55,020 --> 00:26:01,020
 and I want you to answer it in two ways, quietly, within yourself,

491
00:26:01,020 --> 00:26:04,020
 because I want you to answer it honestly.

492
00:26:04,020 --> 00:26:07,020
 I don't want you to fear your anonymity being risked

493
00:26:07,020 --> 00:26:09,020
 and people are going to know.

494
00:26:09,020 --> 00:26:12,020
 I want you to answer it quietly, and I want you to answer it quickly,

495
00:26:12,020 --> 00:26:14,020
 like the first thing that comes to mind.

496
00:26:14,020 --> 00:26:19,020
 Grab hold of that and remember it as we walk through this.

497
00:26:19,020 --> 00:26:23,020
 So here's the question.

