 in the gospels, and we know it.

748
00:38:35,020 --> 00:38:37,020
 And yet our experience of Jesus' love,

749
00:38:37,020 --> 00:38:39,020
 it feels so very different, because when we mess up,

750
00:38:39,020 --> 00:38:41,020
 it's not a voice of mercy that meets us,

751
00:38:41,020 --> 00:38:45,020
 it's a voice of shame.

752
00:38:45,020 --> 00:38:47,020
 When we act in fear, it's not a voice of compassion

753
00:38:47,020 --> 00:38:50,020
 that meets us in that moment, it is a voice of frustration.

754
00:38:50,020 --> 00:38:52,020
 When we hide our sin, it's not a voice of pursuit.

755
00:38:52,020 --> 00:38:54,020
 Instead, it is a voice of judgment.

756
00:38:54,020 --> 00:38:57,020
 When we sin against Jesus, it's not the voice of grace

757
00:38:57,020 --> 00:38:59,020
 that meets us, it's the voice of condemnation.

758
00:38:59,020 --> 00:39:02,020
 But here's the thing, porch, I need you to see it.

759
00:39:02,020 --> 00:39:04,020
 If what we feel from Jesus does not match

760
00:39:04,020 --> 00:39:06,020
 what we know from Jesus in the Bible,

761
00:39:06,020 --> 00:39:09,020
 what it means is we do not know the love of Jesus

762
00:39:09,020 --> 00:39:11,020
 as well as we think.

763
00:39:11,020 --> 00:39:13,020
 We do not know it as well as we think,

764
00:39:13,020 --> 00:39:15,020
 because we are not experiencing it

765
00:39:15,020 --> 00:39:18,020
 as they experienced it.

766
00:39:18,020 --> 00:39:20,020
 Does that make sense?

767
00:39:20,020 --> 00:39:23,020
 That's so important for you to get.

768
00:39:23,020 --> 00:39:25,020
 That's why he has given you his spirit.

769
00:39:25,020 --> 00:39:28,020
 Romans 5:5 says, "And hope does not put us to shame,

770
00:39:28,020 --> 00:39:31,020
 "because God, he has poured his love into our hearts

771
00:39:31,020 --> 00:39:34,020
 "through the Holy Spirit who has been given to us."

772
00:39:34,020 --> 00:39:36,020
 How much does Jesus love you?

773
00:39:36,020 --> 00:39:39,020
 So much so that he has given you the Holy Spirit

774
00:39:39,020 --> 00:39:41,020
 to remind you, hey, I love you.

775
00:39:41,020 --> 00:39:44,020
 Today, yeah, today.

776
00:39:44,020 --> 00:39:47,020
 Tomorrow, yes, tomorrow.

777
00:39:47,020 --> 00:39:50,020
 Next week, yeah, next week.

778
00:39:50,020 --> 00:39:54,020
 This life, yeah, I'm not going anywhere.

779
00:39:54,020 --> 00:39:58,020
 Forever, that's exactly where I'm taking you,

780
00:39:58,020 --> 00:40:00,020
 because I love you.

781
00:40:00,020 --> 00:40:02,020
 God wants to assure you of his love so much

782
00:40:02,020 --> 00:40:05,020
 that he has poured his Holy Spirit into your life

783
00:40:05,020 --> 00:40:12,020
 to declare to you how much he loves you.

784
00:40:12,020 --> 00:40:15,020
 He wants to save you from a life of knowing his love distantly

785
00:40:15,020 --> 00:40:18,020
 but never feeling his love personally.

786
00:40:18,020 --> 00:40:20,020
 If he didn't, why would he enter into a relationship with you?

787
00:40:20,020 --> 00:40:21,020
 Have you ever thought about that?

788
00:40:21,020 --> 00:40:23,020
 Why would Jesus want relationship with you

789
00:40:23,020 --> 00:40:25,020
 if all he wanted was for you to know about him?

790
00:40:25,020 --> 00:40:27,020
 You can know about someone by just reading their story,

791
00:40:27,020 --> 00:40:30,020
 but you cannot feel their love for you

792
00:40:30,020 --> 00:40:32,020
 until you enter into their story.

793
00:40:32,020 --> 00:40:35,020
 So many of us, we've read the story,

794
00:40:35,020 --> 00:40:37,020
 but we have not read ourselves into it.

795
00:40:37,020 --> 00:40:39,020
 The fact that he not only came to save the world,

796
00:40:39,020 --> 00:40:42,020
 he came to save you.

797
00:40:42,020 --> 00:40:46,020
 Last point, and we're going to have to go fast.

798
00:40:46,020 --> 00:40:48,020
 Verse 19, he says, "That you may be filled

799
00:40:48,020 --> 00:40:49,020
 with all the fullness of God."

800
00:40:49,020 --> 00:40:51,020
 Here's the thing, we're all full of something, okay?

801
00:40:51,020 --> 00:40:53,020
 Some of you, you're full of stress.

802
00:40:53,020 --> 00:40:55,020
 Others of you, you're full of disappointment.

803
00:40:55,020 --> 00:40:57,020
 Others, you're full of anxiety.

804
00:40:57,020 --> 00:40:58,020
 Others, it's frustration.

805
00:40:58,020 --> 00:41:00,020
 Some, it's regret.

806
00:41:00,020 --> 00:41:01,020
 Contrary to what most people say,

807
00:41:01,020 --> 00:41:03,020
 the world does not leave you empty.

808
00:41:03,020 --> 00:41:06,020
 In fact, it is filling you up with something

809
00:41:06,020 --> 00:41:08,020
 and the wrong thing.

810
00:41:08,020 --> 00:41:09,020
 When I was in high school,

811
00:41:09,020 --> 00:41:12,020
 I took my dad's truck to go and get some gas.

812
00:41:12,020 --> 00:41:16,020
 By nature of my own habit, I hopped out of the truck,

813
00:41:16,020 --> 00:41:18,020
 swiped my card, I grabbed the pump,

814
00:41:18,020 --> 00:41:23,020
 and I proceeded to put gasoline into his diesel excursion.

815
00:41:23,020 --> 00:41:28,020
 I was putting the wrong thing in his truck.

816
00:41:28,020 --> 00:41:31,020
 I was filling it with that which would not help it,

817
00:41:31,020 --> 00:41:32,020
 but hurt it.

818
00:41:32,020 --> 00:41:34,020
 Many of you are filling yourself with things

819
00:41:34,020 --> 00:41:37,020
 that will not help you, but will hurt you.

820
00:41:37,020 --> 00:41:39,020
 Some of you, you have a habit

821
00:41:39,020 --> 00:41:41,020
 of pumping the wrong thing into your life.

822
00:41:41,020 --> 00:41:44,020
 And yet, here's the thing, my dad, he showed up,

823
00:41:44,020 --> 00:41:47,020
 and he helped me siphon the gas from his tank.

824
00:41:47,020 --> 00:41:48,020
 Jesus has shown up,

825
00:41:48,020 --> 00:41:52,020
 and he has come to siphon the sin out of your soul.

826
00:41:52,020 --> 00:41:53,020
 He wants to help you.

827
00:41:53,020 --> 00:41:55,020
 He wants to move you back into right relationship,

828
00:41:55,020 --> 00:41:59,020
 because Jesus gives fulfillment where the world cannot.

829
00:41:59,020 --> 00:42:03,020
 He gives fulfillment where the world cannot.

830
00:42:03,020 --> 00:42:06,020
 And here's the thing, we are all looking for fulfillment.

831
00:42:06,020 --> 00:42:09,020
 What you need to know is fulfillment came looking for you.

832
00:42:09,020 --> 00:42:11,020
 Fulfillment is not something you attain.

833
00:42:11,020 --> 00:42:13,020
 It is something you appreciate,

834
00:42:13,020 --> 00:42:15,020
 because you already have it if you have him.

835
00:42:15,020 --> 00:42:18,020
 I love the way Charles Spurgeon described this lesson

836
00:42:18,020 --> 00:42:19,020
 as he was teaching a friend.

837
00:42:19,020 --> 00:42:21,020
 He took that friend to the edge of the ocean,

838
00:42:21,020 --> 00:42:25,020
 and he took an empty bottle, unscrewed its lid,

839
00:42:25,020 --> 00:42:28,020
 and plunged it into the depth of the ocean.

840
00:42:28,020 --> 00:42:30,020
 And as he pulled it forward, and he showed it to his friend,

841
00:42:30,020 --> 00:42:33,020
 he said, "This bottle, or the fullness of the ocean

842
00:42:33,020 --> 00:42:35,020
 "is in this bottle."

843
00:42:35,020 --> 00:42:39,020
 And he proceeded to take the bottle, put on its cap,

844
00:42:39,020 --> 00:42:42,020
 and then throw the bottle into the ocean.

845
00:42:42,020 --> 00:42:45,020
 And he said, "All the fullness of the bottle

846
00:42:45,020 --> 00:42:47,020
 "is now in the ocean."

847
00:42:47,020 --> 00:42:49,020
 That's the nature of relationship with Jesus.

848
00:42:49,020 --> 00:42:51,020
 All of his fullness is in you,

849
00:42:51,020 --> 00:42:53,020
 and all of your fullness is in him.

850
00:42:53,020 --> 00:42:56,020
 He wants to be intimately, intricately intertwined with you.

851
00:42:56,020 --> 00:42:59,020
 That's how deep his love is,

852
00:42:59,020 --> 00:43:03,020
 and how big his heart wants for you.

853
00:43:03,020 --> 00:43:08,020
 How do you know the love of God?

854
00:43:08,020 --> 00:43:12,020
 You look to him who came to give you life,

855
00:43:12,020 --> 00:43:14,020
 and life to the full.

856
00:43:14,020 --> 00:43:17,020
 Some of that sounds too good to be true.

857
00:43:17,020 --> 00:43:19,020
 It sounds too impossible to believe.

858
00:43:19,020 --> 00:43:21,020
 It's too unreasonable to consider.

859
00:43:21,020 --> 00:43:23,020
 And yet you need to know the way Paul ends

860
00:43:23,020 --> 00:43:25,020
 is the right answer for you,

861
00:43:25,020 --> 00:43:27,020
 not to him who is able to do far more abundantly

862
00:43:27,020 --> 00:43:29,020
 than all we ask or think.

863
00:43:29,020 --> 00:43:31,020
 Truth of the matter is, this is too good to be true.

864
00:43:31,020 --> 00:43:33,020
 It is too unbelievable to consider.

865
00:43:33,020 --> 00:43:36,020
 It is too impossible to be true.

866
00:43:36,020 --> 00:43:40,020
 And yet God has made a business of doing the unbelievable.

867
00:43:40,020 --> 00:43:43,020
 He delights in the impossible.

868
00:43:43,020 --> 00:43:48,020
 He walks in the ways that are unreasonable to the world.

869
00:43:48,020 --> 00:43:51,020
 He has come to give you strength in place of exhaustion

870
00:43:51,020 --> 00:43:53,020
 through the love of his son,

871
00:43:53,020 --> 00:43:56,020
 who came to give you life in place of death.

872
00:43:56,020 --> 00:43:59,020
 He has come to give you acceptance and not rejection.

873
00:43:59,020 --> 00:44:01,020
 Though all of us were dead in our sin,

874
00:44:01,020 --> 00:44:03,020
 separated from God,

875
00:44:03,020 --> 00:44:08,020
 he sent his son to bring us back into relationship with himself.

876
00:44:08,020 --> 00:44:11,020
 He has given a love that is bigger than bored belief,

877
00:44:11,020 --> 00:44:14,020
 a love that doesn't just lead you to want to believe in him,

878
00:44:14,020 --> 00:44:18,020
 but wants you to be with him forever.

879
00:44:18,020 --> 00:44:20,020
 He has come to give you fullness

880
00:44:20,020 --> 00:44:22,020
 where the world cannot give you fullness.

881
00:44:22,020 --> 00:44:26,020
 For Christ, he came to give you what the world and you yourself could not give you.

882
00:44:26,020 --> 00:44:33,020
 He came to give you life, even at the cost of his own self.

883
00:44:33,020 --> 00:44:35,020
 Do you want to know?

884
00:44:35,020 --> 00:44:38,020
 Do you want to feel the love you know?

885
00:44:38,020 --> 00:44:41,020
 You were here and you've heard of this love.

886
00:44:41,020 --> 00:44:44,020
 If you want to feel the love you know,

887
00:44:44,020 --> 00:44:48,020
 then you have to know the love he felt.

888
00:44:48,020 --> 00:44:50,020
 The love he felt for you,

889
00:44:50,020 --> 00:44:52,020
 the lengths he'd go to get to you,

890
00:44:52,020 --> 00:44:54,020
 the life he would offer up in your place,

891
00:44:54,020 --> 00:44:57,020
 the death he would die so you would not have to,

892
00:44:57,020 --> 00:45:00,020
 the resurrection he would take up,

893
00:45:00,020 --> 00:45:03,020
 declaring that as he rises, you can rise with him.

894
00:45:03,020 --> 00:45:05,020
 If only you place your faith in him.

895
00:45:05,020 --> 00:45:08,020
 Do you want a love like this?

896
00:45:08,020 --> 00:45:09,020
 It's not out there.

897
00:45:09,020 --> 00:45:11,020
 It's right here.

898
00:45:11,020 --> 00:45:12,020
 Place your faith in him.

899
00:45:12,020 --> 00:45:13,020
 Let me pray.

900
00:45:13,020 --> 00:45:14,020
 Jesus, thanks for tonight.

901
00:45:14,020 --> 00:45:16,020
 Thank you for your love.

902
00:45:16,020 --> 00:45:18,020
 We want to sing to you.

903
00:45:18,020 --> 00:45:22,020
 We want to delight in what you've worked on us here this evening.

904
00:45:22,020 --> 00:45:25,020
 And God, I feel, just transparently,

905
00:45:25,020 --> 00:45:27,020
 the need to get off of this stage.

906
00:45:27,020 --> 00:45:30,020
 The timer's going quick.

907
00:45:30,020 --> 00:45:34,020
 And yet, Lord, I don't want to rush past what you may be doing.

908
00:45:34,020 --> 00:45:36,020
 I think, God, you might be stirring.

909
00:45:36,020 --> 00:45:39,020
 No, God, I believe you are stirring.

910
00:45:39,020 --> 00:45:43,020
 There are some here that hear this call,

911
00:45:43,020 --> 00:45:45,020
 that agree with the description.

912
00:45:45,020 --> 00:45:46,020
 That has been my life.

913
00:45:46,020 --> 00:45:48,020
 My life has been one where I have known the love of God,

914
00:45:48,020 --> 00:45:50,020
 and yet I have not felt the love of God.

915
00:45:50,020 --> 00:45:52,020
 And yet here tonight, I'm hearing you.

916
00:45:52,020 --> 00:45:54,020
 Like that love, it offers strength.

917
00:45:54,020 --> 00:45:56,020
 That love, it offers acceptance.

918
00:45:56,020 --> 00:45:58,020
 That love, it offers weight.

919
00:45:58,020 --> 00:45:59,020
 And that love, it offers fulfillment.

920
00:45:59,020 --> 00:46:00,020
 I want that.

921
00:46:00,020 --> 00:46:02,020
 I want that kind of love.

922
00:46:02,020 --> 00:46:04,020
 And you need look no longer.

923
00:46:04,020 --> 00:46:07,020
 If you want that kind of love, that love has come looking for you.

924
00:46:07,020 --> 00:46:09,020
 You need only place your faith in Christ.

925
00:46:09,020 --> 00:46:11,020
 Others of you, you've already done so,

926
00:46:11,020 --> 00:46:16,020
 and yet you find that your spirituality is more characterized by mediocrity

927
00:46:16,020 --> 00:46:19,020
 than significance.

928
00:46:19,020 --> 00:46:23,020
 You can change that all tonight by simply confessing that to him,

929
00:46:23,020 --> 00:46:24,020
 asking him for more,

930
00:46:24,020 --> 00:46:28,020
 and believing the fact that he has come to give you more than you already have.

931
00:46:28,020 --> 00:46:30,020
 But, Jesus, we want you to work in us now.

932
00:46:30,020 --> 00:46:32,020
 Would you take over the space?

933
00:46:32,020 --> 00:46:33,020
 Would you move in us?

934
00:46:33,020 --> 00:46:35,020
 We pray it's in your name.

935
00:46:35,020 --> 00:46:36,020
 Amen.

